Conditional Rendering
The && (short-circuit) method is used when you want to display something only if a condition is true.
The ternary operator is used when you want to choose between two different outputs (if true or false).
The if/else statement is used before returning JSX when the logic is more complex.
Early return is used to immediately return a result if a condition is not met, making the code cleaner and easier to read.

